K-Means Clustering

Author: David Saucedo Date: Oct 5, 2022

image info

DEFINITION OF KEY CONCEPTS

K-Means Clustering main goal is to identify data patterns and cluster data observations into different groups based on their similarities. It is worth mentioning that K-Means Clustering is an unsupervised clustering algorithm. It is also very useful when working with a dataset characterized by no labels.

it is worth mentioning that k-means clustering analysis can only include quantitative variables

rh_edad<-rh_alt %>% select(genero,estado_civil,salario_diario,edad)

The normalizing of a dataset (quantitative variables) using the mean value and standard deviation is performed by scale()

rh_edad_norm<-scale(rh_edad[3:4])

Use fviz function to view Elbow Plot for visualizing optimal number of clusters

fviz_nbclust() helps to determine and visualize the optimal number of clusters

fviz_nbclust(rh_edad_norm, kmeans, method="wss")+ # wss method considers total within sum of square
  geom_vline(xintercept=4, linetype=2)+           # optimal number of clusters is computed with the default method = "euclidean"
  labs(subtitle = "Elbow method")

How to Select the Optimal Number of Clusters?

The within-cluster sum of squares is a measure of the variability of the observations within each cluster. In general, a cluster that has a small sum of squares is more compact than a cluster that has a large sum of squares. Generally, we select the optimal value of K when we see SSE starts to flatten out and forms an elbow shape.

Main Insights

  • K-means clustering is estimated by considering the variables edad and salario_diario from the FORM - Recursos Humanos dataset. In so doing, there is a selection of 4 clusters by using The Elbow Method.

  • Based on the edad variable, the 4 selected clusters are called: 1) Jubilicacin, 2) Avanzada, 3) Adulta, and 4) Joven. Cluster Jubilacin includes most of the number of observations of our dataset whereas Cluster Avanzada includes the fewest number of observtions.

  • Maximum age in years by clusters names are the following: 1) Jubilicacin (72), Avanzada (60), Adulta (38), and Joven (34).

  • Clusters Jubilacin y Avanazada display the greatest dispersion in terms of age. It is also worth noticing that the Cluster Jubilicacin shows the greatest dispersion related to daily wage.

  • According to the scatterplot, it looks like daily wages are very similar across clusters, however, the Cluster Jubilicacin shows a weak but positive relationship between age and daily wages.

  • In terms of gender, cluster Jublicacin is mainly characterized by women whereas Cluster Adulta is characterized by men.

  • Lastly but not least, Ayudante General is the most common job position in FORM, particularly in Cluster Adulta. On average, Ayudante General is characterized by a daily wage of $182 and 26 years old.
